article.headline: UNC Wilmington 59, East Carolina 44
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. (AP) -- Todd Hendley scored seven of his game-high 15 points during an 11-2 stretch late in the second half to lead UNC Wilmington to a 59-44 victory over East Carolina on Tuesday night. Hendley made 5-for-11 from the field and converted all five of his free throw attempts for the Seahawks (3-4). Montez Downey scored 14 points. John Fields led the Pirates (4-3) with 12 points on 5-of-6 from the floor and a pair of free throws. The Pirates trailed by just four points in the second half when UNC Wilmington went on the 11-2 run, sparked by a basket by Hendley with 10:16 remaining. Vladimir Kuljanin's putback at 1:25 put the Seahawks ahead 57-42.
